@startuml
title Robustness - View Meetup Details

left to right direction
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false

rectangle "Boundary Layer" {
  object "MeetupDetailView\n<<boundary>>" as B
}

rectangle "Control Layer" {
  object "MeetupController\n<<control>>" as C
  object "MeetupService\n<<control>>" as S
}

rectangle "Entity Layer" {
  object "Meetup\n<<entity>>" as M
  object "Participation\n<<entity>>" as P
  object "Location\n<<entity>>" as L
}

rectangle "External" {
  object "MeetupRepository\n<<entity>>" as R
}

B -> C : 1 openDetails(meetupId)
C -> S : 2 getMeetupDetails(meetupId)
S -> R : 3 loadMeetup(meetupId)
R -> S : 4 meetup
S -> M : 5 readCoreDetails()
S -> P : 6 readParticipants()
S -> L : 7 readLocation()
S -> C : 8 detailsDTO
C -> B : 9 showDetails()

note bottom
User selects a meetup. Controller asks service for full details. Service loads meetup,
reads participants and location data, and returns a complete view model to display.
end note

@enduml